   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="body:1;4:10">
         

         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="p:1;7:13">In service mode, the HB20 device does not run the application contained in flash. Instead, it automatically enables (connects) the GPIO inputs for the SPI2AHB, JTAG7, and UART0 interfaces so they can be used to access the device and program an application into the flash, if desired. For more information regarding the GPIO in service mode, see <xref href="GeneralPurposeIOGPIODefaultConfigurationsd1e25219.xml#GeneralPurposeIOGPIODefaultConfigurationsd1e25219" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="xref:1;7:475" type="topic"><?ditaot usertext?>General-Purpose IO (GPIO) Default Configurations </xref>.</p>
