         <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="p:3;9:13">Service mode is invoked by holding WUP_EN high for at least t<sub class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sub " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="sub:1;9:79">PR1</sub> or t<sub class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sub " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="sub:2;9:98">PR2</sub> after RESET_B is toggled low or after applying VBATT voltage, which causes the POR to operate. Please refer to table <xref href="ElectricalSpecificationsd1e3187.xml#ElectricalSpecificationsd1e3187/SupplyRampUpTimeRequirementsandProcessorStartUpTimeCharacteristicsd1e4344" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="xref:2;9:380" type="table"><?ditaot usertext?>Supply Ramp Up Time Requirements and Processor Start-Up Time Characteristics</xref> for the timing requirements of t<sub class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sub " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="sub:3;9:501">PR1</sub> or t<sub class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sub " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\HB20Datasheet\ServiceModed1e3151.xml" xtrc="sub:4;9:520">PR2.</sub>
